   <body>
      <context>
         <note>This menu is only available if ECO mode is enabled.</note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>From the <uicontrol>Main Menu</uicontrol>, select <menucascade>
                  <uicontrol>System Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Bypass Control</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> using the UP/DOWN keys and the ENTER key. </p>
            <stepxmp>
               <table outputclass="font:10">
                  <tgroup cols="1">
                     <colspec colname="col1"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <screen xml:space="preserve">Confirm action:UPS into ECO Mode NO, Abort►YES, UPS into ECO Mode</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select <uicontrol>YES, UPS into ECO Mode</uicontrol> to
transfer to ECO mode. The following message will appear on the display:</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <table outputclass="font:10">
                  <tgroup cols="1">
                     <colspec colname="col1"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <screen xml:space="preserve">The load is supplied via the static bypass switch</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>After the transfer to ECO mode is complete, press the ESC
key.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
